KENNEDY v. MANHATTAN RY. CO. (Supreme Court, General Term, First Department. December 15, 1893.) Action by Hannah Kennedy, as administratrix, etc., against the Manhattan Railway Company.

Argued before VAN BRUNT, P. J„ and FOLLETT and PARKER, JJ.

David Leventritt, for plaintiff. Davies & Rapallo, for defendant.

No opinion. Motion denied, with $10 costs. See 25 N. Y. Supp. 1123.
